Value Sign # 4: Return on Equity (ROE)- Look for a return on equity that is consistently high, compared with the return for other companies in the same industry as well as the average of sector industry, or that shows a strong pattern of growth. A steady return on equity of more than 15% may be a sign of a company that knows how to manage itself well. ROE is calculated as the companyโs net profit divided by the companyโs equity balance as reported in the Balance Sheet. Stock will be attractive for investors, if the companyโs ROE is growing year after year then the stock's price will tend to show long-term strength.\t


